params._aggregator: The address of the deployed AMMAggregator contract.
params._feeController: The address of the deployed FeeController contract.
params._multisig: The address for Ownable pattern (e.g., a Gnosis Safe).
params._vault: The address of the deployed VaultSpot contract.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

swap(address,address,uint256,uint256,byt.details: This is the primary function for users to interact with the swap functionality.      It debits tokens from the user's vault balance, calculates and deducts fees,      executes the swap, and credits the output tokens back to the user's vault balance.

params.amountIn: The amount of `tokenIn` to be swapped.
params.data: Additional data to be passed to the adapter (if any).
params.minAmountOut: The minimum amount of `tokenOut` expected to be received.
params.tokenIn: The address of the token to be swapped.
params.tokenOut: The address of the token to be received.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

swap(address,address,uint256,uint256,byt.notice: Executes a swap using the best available route found by the AMMAggregator.
